    <section id="content">
      <section id="main">
        <p id="intro">
          BaseApp is a Mac OS X menubar application that helps you stay on top of everything what happens in your <a href="http://basecamphq.com/">Basecamp</a> accounts.
        </p>

        <ul id="features">
          <li>
            <h2>Feels right at home</h2>

            <p>
              Designed to be as minimalistic as possible, <strong>BaseApp</strong> feels right at home on Mac OS X. Mimicking a menu bar item it feels like it&rsquo;s part of your Mac.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h2>There when you need it</h2>

            <p>
              We worked very hard making sure you only see <strong>BaseApp</strong> when you need it. It sits in the background monitoring your Basecamp accounts for activity.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h2>Give your inbox a break</h2>

            <p>
              We built <strong>BaseApp</strong> because our inbox was overflowing with Basecamp emails. Disable these notifications and let BaseApp take it from there.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h2>Notifications</h2>

            <p>
              <strong>BaseApp</strong> supports <a href="http://growl.info/">Growl</a> and/or sound notifications. It&rsquo;s up to you to customize the way <em>you</em> want to be notified of new activity.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>

